---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Reproducibility">
  <h1>Reproducibility</h1>
  <p class="page-intro">
    Instructions for reproducing our experiments and evaluation pipeline.
  </p>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Environment Setup</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Python 3.10+</li>
        <li>CUDA 11.8+ (GPU recommended)</li>
        <li>16GB+ RAM</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Installation</h3>
      <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/narekmeliqsetyan/motion-aware-video-editing.git
cd motion-aware-video-editing
pip install -r requirements.txt</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Running the Pipeline</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>1. Object Segmentation</h3>
      <pre><code>python segment.py --input video.mp4 --model sam2 --prompt "object to replace"</code></pre>

      <h3>2. Video Inpainting</h3>
      <pre><code>python inpaint.py --input video.mp4 --masks masks/ --output inpainted.mp4</code></pre>

      <h3>3. Object Insertion + Warping</h3>
      <pre><code>python insert.py --background inpainted.mp4 --object replacement.png --output final.mp4</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Evaluation</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Metrics Computation</h3>
      <pre><code>python evaluate.py --pred results/ --gt ground_truth/ --metrics iou dice ssim lpips fid</code></pre>

      <h3>Metric Definitions</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>IoU</strong> — Intersection over Union of predicted and ground-truth masks</li>
        <li><strong>Dice</strong> — Dice coefficient (F1 score of mask overlap)</li>
        <li><strong>SSIM</strong> — Structural Similarity Index of inpainted frames</li>
        <li><strong>LPIPS</strong> — Learned Perceptual Image Patch Similarity (lower is better)</li>
        <li><strong>FID</strong> — Frechet Inception Distance of generated objects (lower is better)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Expected Results</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        With the default configuration and provided test videos, you should
        obtain results within the following ranges:
      </p>
      <table class="results-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Metric</th>
            <th>SAM2 + ProPainter</th>
            <th>YOLO + ProPainter</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>IoU</td><td>0.85 - 0.92</td><td>0.71 - 0.85</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Dice</td><td>0.89 - 0.96</td><td>0.80 - 0.91</td></tr>
          <tr><td>SSIM</td><td>0.78 - 0.88</td><td>0.70 - 0.82</td></tr>
          <tr><td>LPIPS</td><td>0.05 - 0.10</td><td>0.10 - 0.18</td></tr>
          <tr><td>FID</td><td>10 - 15</td><td>15 - 22</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Troubleshooting</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>CUDA out of memory</strong> — Reduce batch size or use CPU mode with <code>--device cpu</code></li>
        <li><strong>SAM2 checkpoint not found</strong> — Download from the <a href="https://github.com/facebookresearch/sam2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">official repo</a></li>
        <li><strong>Low-quality inpainting</strong> — Ensure masks cover the full object; dilate masks by 5-10 pixels</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-intro {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }
  h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  li { margin-bottom: var(--space-xs); }
  .results-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .results-table th,
  .results-table td {
    padding: var(--space-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .results-table th {
    background: var(--c-surface);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
